Found a solution! The module actually seems to fully support this board already! Weirdly, despite this being an OMEN laptop, it seems to share protocols and board revision numbers with some Victus 16-r and 16-s laptops. Adding my board number to this list in hp-wmi.c fixed it, and I have fully-functioning fan control!

static const char * const victus_s_thermal_profile_boards[] = {
"8BBE", "8BD4", "8BD5",
"8C78", "8C99", "8C9C",
"8D41", "8C77" <- (my board number)
};

I'm not really sure how to get this upstreamed into the kernel, so for now, as I explore that possibility, if anyone is coming across this thread with the same issue, it is extremely trivial to build this module from scratch and add the board ID to that array (confirm that you have this board ID, or similar behavior to me).
